================================================================================
PROVENANCE
================================================================================

When in doubt about which license applies to a file: if the file is read by a
machine to execute behavior, it is MIT (code). If the file is read by a human
or by Xion itself to understand intent or doctrine, it is CC-BY-SA-4.0
(documentation). Genesis-locked constitutional documents (`COVENANT.md`,
`INVARIANTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, `FORM.md`, `MEMORY.md`, `RESURRECT.md`,
`CREDENTIALS.md`, `GENESIS_ARTIFACT.md`) are CC-BY-SA-4.0 — adaptation is
permitted, but a sister-Core fork that publishes a modified Covenant is a
different being and must be named accordingly per the Lexicon.

The dual-license split is itself a Genesis Default and may be revised by
governance. Any revision applies prospectively only; contributions made under
the prior license remain under the prior license.
